1. Word Embedding
  ----------------

What is it?

Computers cannot understand words directly. They understand only numbers.

Word Embedding converts every word into a vector (list of numbers) while preserving its meaning.

Example

Sentence:

I love AI

Without embedding:

I     → 1
love  → 2
AI    → 3

These numbers don't tell the computer that love is similar to like.

With Word Embedding:

love → [0.25, 0.91, 0.42]
like → [0.27, 0.89, 0.40]
hate → [0.85, 0.11, 0.73]

Here,

love and like have similar vectors.
hate has a different vector.

So the computer understands similarity between words.

Real-time Example

Google Search understands that

Car ≈ Automobile

even if the exact word isn't used.

Popular Embeddings
Word2Vec
