2. LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)
   -----------------------------

What is it?

LSTM is a special type of Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) that remembers important information from earlier words in a sentence.

Why is it needed?

Sentence:

I grew up in Chennai.
Now I work in Bangalore.
I miss my hometown.

To understand "my hometown", the model should remember Chennai from the first sentence.

A normal RNN often forgets long-term information.

LSTM remembers it.

Real-time Example

Predicting the next word:

I am going to

↓

school
office
market

LSTM uses previous words to predict the next one.

Applications
Sentiment Analysis
Spam Detection
Text Classification
Speech Recognition


======================

3. Sequence-to-Sequence (Seq2Seq)
   -----------------------------


What is it?

Seq2Seq converts one sequence into another sequence.

Input = Sequence

↓

Output = Another Sequence

Example 1

English

How are you?

↓

Tamil

நீங்கள் எப்படி இருக்கிறீர்கள்?
Example 2

Question

What is AI?

↓

Answer

Artificial Intelligence is...
Architecture
Input Sentence
       ↓
Encoder (LSTM)
       ↓
Context Vector
       ↓
Decoder (LSTM)
       ↓
Output Sentence

Applications

Machine Translation
Chatbots
Text Summarization
Question Answering

======================

4. Transformer
   ------------


What is it?

Transformer is the modern Deep Learning architecture for NLP.

Instead of reading words one by one like LSTM, it processes all words in parallel using a mechanism called Self-Attention.

Example

Sentence:

The boy who won the race is happy.

The Transformer understands that "won" refers to "boy", even though other words are in between.

Advantages

Faster than LSTM
Better at understanding context
Handles long documents well
Can be trained on huge datasets
Popular Transformer Models
BERT
GPT
T5
RoBERTa
BART
